A vast factory conveyor belt stretching into the distance, carrying hundreds of identical glowing blue lotus flowers in transparent capsules, each capsule smoothly sliding into place on the belt. The scene is rendered in Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures, warm golden afternoon light streaming through tall industrial windows, gentle dust motes floating in the air. The factory has an organic, almost whimsical quality with curved pipes and brass fittings covered in trailing ivy. Small mechanical arms delicately guide each capsule along its path. The perspective draws the eye from a single capsule in the foreground toward the horizon where countless more await distribution, suggesting effortless mass deployment with a touch of magic and care.
